body_html: I don't think so (why would it have a version counter?). Apart from that, arrays returned from multiple .numpy() calls have nothing in common (from NumPy's point of view), and so even if the counters existed, they could easily get out of sync.

body: I don't think so (why *would* it have a version counter?). Apart from that, arrays returned from multiple `.numpy()` calls have nothing in common (from NumPy's point of view), and so even if the counters existed, they could easily get out of sync.
